President Obama's fiscal policy speech promises to protect working people from the Republican agenda that leads to job loss and declining standards. He emphasizes the importance of Social Security, Medicare, and Medicaid to working people and opposes any cuts to these programs. The focus should be on job creation, as it is key to long-term deficit reduction. The Republican budget proposal is criticized for favoring the wealthy and corporations at the expense of the middle class and poor. The deficit cannot be addressed until fairness is restored to the tax system and corporate tax loopholes are closed. President Obama is urged to find a balance between spending cuts and new revenue to avoid burdening the poor and middle class. The Fiscal Commission Chairs' plan is seen as regressive and economically destructive. Democrats propose alternative plans that prioritize fiscal health, tax fairness, and investments in the future.